    "content": [
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you've ever sat through a slide deck that felt like watching paint dry, you know the problem: most presentations are linear, flat, and forgettable. Prezi has always been the antidote to that monotony, and their latest features push things even further.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I've been following Prezi's evolution for years, and what they've shipped recently genuinely excites me. The new AI-powered tools, combined with their signature zoom-and-move canvas, make it possible to build presentations that look like a professional designer touched every frame. And you don't need design skills to pull it off.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "*Disclosure: This post contains affiliate links. If you purchase through them, I may earn a commission at no extra cost to you.*",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Let's break down what's new, what makes Prezi different, and whether it's the right fit for your next presentation.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
