          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Why Prezi's Zoom Canvas Still Wins",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Before AI entered the picture, Prezi's core differentiator was its non-linear canvas. Instead of clicking through slides one by one, you move across a single large canvas, zooming into topics and pulling back to show the big picture.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "This matters more than people realize. When you zoom into a detail and then zoom out to show how it connects to the whole, your audience *remembers* it. Research backs this up—spatial storytelling activates different parts of the brain compared to static slides.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The new features build on this foundation:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Smoother transitions",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ": The zoom animations are more fluid, with better motion controls so nothing feels jarring.",
            "marks": []
